       "functools.cache.__code__.co_name.__eq__('cache') == True — cache is a pure-Python function in Lib/functools.py; its code object co_name records the function name 'cache' (5 chars); str.__eq__('cache') returns True; no prior functools spec checks cache.__code__.co_name via functoolsextra87; new to extra87"]

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# cache __code__ co_argcount and partial __qualname__ string equality — extra87
#
# Wave 246 theme: cache code argcount and partial __qualname__ string equality.
#
# functools.cache.__code__.co_argcount              == 1
# functools.partial.__qualname__.__eq__('partial')  == True
# functools.wraps.__qualname__.__eq__('wraps')      == True
